<subSubSection id="33EB65062102FF96B1DCFB018AC0FAB9" pageId="5" pageNumber="196" type="description">
<paragraph id="7B4E368D2102FF96B1DCFB018AC0FAB9" blockId="5.[163,1070,1255,1336]" pageId="5" pageNumber="196">
Comment: The distribution of 
<taxonomicName id="BCF14D0E2102FF96B34BFB0E8AB6FB7C" baseAuthorityName="BERNHAUER" baseAuthorityYear="1931" box="[564,742,1256,1277]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lobrathium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="196" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hongkongense">
<emphasis id="4985EA9F2102FF96B34BFB0E8AB6FB7C" box="[564,742,1256,1277]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="196">L. hongkongense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the most widespread species among East Palaearctic 
<taxonomicName id="BCF14D0E2102FF96B0DFFAE38A47FA9B" authorityName="MULSANT &amp; REY" authorityYear="1878" box="[416,535,1285,1306]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lobrathium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="196" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4985EA9F2102FF96B0DFFAE38A47FA9B" box="[416,535,1285,1306]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="196">Lobrathium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, is mapped in 
<bibRefCitation id="1F604B7C2102FF96B3C4FAE38B08FA9A" author="ASSING V" box="[699,856,1285,1307]" pageId="5" pageNumber="196" pagination="49 - 128" refId="ref8487" refString="ASSING V. (2012): A revision of East Palaearctic Lobrathium (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Paederinae). - Bonn Zoological Bulletin 61 (1): 49 - 128." type="journal article" year="2012">ASSING (2012)</bibRefCitation>
. Some of the above specimens collected in May and July are teneral.
</paragraph>
